##-> Allows the firewall host to open chat conntections to server on the 
##-> outside network. It is assumed that the IRC server listens
##-> on the often used default port 6667.
##-> These rules maybe useful for a personal firewall.
@IPCHAINS@ -A output -i @EXTDEV@ -s @EXTIP@ 1024:65535 -d @EXTNET@ 6667 -p tcp -j ACCEPT
@IPCHAINS@ -A input -i @EXTDEV@ -s @EXTNET@ 6667 -d @EXTIP@ 1024:65535 ! -y -p tcp -j ACCEPT
